title: Polish community tuck into doughnuts as they celebrate 'Fat Thursday'
text:
23 February 2017 at 4:30pm Polish community tuck into doughnuts as they celebrate 'Fat Thursday' 
The Channel Island's Polish community have been tucking into doughnuts today, as they celebrate 'Fat Thursday'. 
The day is all about eating fatty foods ahead of the first day of fasting, Ash Wednesday, which is next week. 
Karolina Klonowska, a St Helier caf√© owner, said non-Polish islanders have also been interested in the holiday.
